# API keys for SEO-AUDIT-OS
# Copy this file to .env and fill in only the keys you actually have.
# Every key is optional. The audit pipeline gracefully skips any dimension
# whose key is missing - no errors raised, no broken PDF. The final report
# renders against whatever data was collected, so a free-mode run still
# produces a complete client deliverable.
# .env itself is gitignored and stays on your machine.

# ===== Required for paid-mode SERP / rankings =====
# Serper.dev (SERP captures, organic results, AI Overview detection,
# competitor identification). If missing, paid-mode falls back to free-mode.
SERPER_API_KEY=

# ===== Google APIs =====
# One key serves PageSpeed Insights, CrUX, Places, and Cloud NL.
# If missing, those four checks are skipped silently and the PDF
# still renders against the on-site crawl + Serper data.
GOOGLE_API_KEY=
GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=



# ===== Optional Semrush integration =====
# When set, the audit pulls the site's Domain Authority + estimated monthly
# organic traffic and surfaces them on the index page stat cards.
# Without the key, those tiles are simply omitted - no error.
SEMRUSH_API_KEY=

# ===== Other paid integrations (all optional) =====
# Moz API (backlinks + DA/PA + keyword difficulty)
MOZ_ACCESS_ID=
MOZ_SECRET_KEY=


